<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,694,1079]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">
Frontal prominence much shorter than wide at base. Face with long paraface and large or deep anterior tentorial pit. Facial tubercle weak to nearly absent. Eye bare. Pile on thorax and tergites rather long. Basisternum (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1428,730,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 49 – 55. 49 – 52" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1746,1768]" captionTargetBox="[335,1213,1140,1715]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[313,1273,1134,1724]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49 – 55. 49 – 52 Procoxa of Cerioidini species, posterior view: 49 Ceriana conopsoides, male, Russia 50 Ceriana vespiformis, male, Montenegro 51 Primocerioides regale, female, Cyprus 52 Sphiximorpha subsessilis, male, The Netherlands. 53 Basisternum of Ceriana conopsoides, frontal view, male, Russia 54 Mesotrochanter of Ceriana caesarea, ventral view, male, Turkmenistan 55 Basisternum of Sphiximorpha subsessilis, frontal view, male, Greece. Scale line = 0.5 mm (a: 49, 50; b: 51, 52; c: 53 – 55)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167932/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
) higher than wide, with nearly straight dorsal margin and two triangular lobes on ventral margin. Anepisternum and anepimeron separated by a membranous area. Metasternum long pilose without modifications. Procoxa (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1428,802,827]" captionStart="FIGURES 49 – 55. 49 – 52" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1746,1768]" captionTargetBox="[335,1213,1140,1715]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[313,1273,1134,1724]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49 – 55. 49 – 52 Procoxa of Cerioidini species, posterior view: 49 Ceriana conopsoides, male, Russia 50 Ceriana vespiformis, male, Montenegro 51 Primocerioides regale, female, Cyprus 52 Sphiximorpha subsessilis, male, The Netherlands. 53 Basisternum of Ceriana conopsoides, frontal view, male, Russia 54 Mesotrochanter of Ceriana caesarea, ventral view, male, Turkmenistan 55 Basisternum of Sphiximorpha subsessilis, frontal view, male, Greece. Scale line = 0.5 mm (a: 49, 50; b: 51, 52; c: 53 – 55)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167932/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) broad, about as wide as long, with a short groove dorsally. Postmetacoxal bridge incomplete. Dorsal lobe of calypter with a fringe of short and rather dense pile. Tergite II somewhat longer than wide, slightly constricted anteromedially. Callus of tergite I absent. Callus of sternite I elongate, oval and partly sclerotized. Genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 148 – 150" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1375,1397]" captionTargetBox="[328,1250,237,1340]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[313,1273,193,1354]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 148 – 150. Male genitalia of Sphiximorpha euprosopa, holotype 148 Epandrium and hypandrium, lateral view 149 Epandrium, dorsal view 150 Epandrium, ventral view. Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167953/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Figs 148–150</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[264,367,946,971]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 157 – 160" captionStart-1="FIGURES 161 – 165" captionStartId-0="45.[151,264,1610,1632]" captionStartId-1="48.[151,264,1209,1231]" captionTargetBox-0="[335,1222,470,1569]" captionTargetBox-1="[326,1235,229,1126]" captionTargetId-0="figure@45.[313,1273,447,1588]" captionTargetId-1="figure@48.[313,1273,193,1188]" captionTargetPageId-0="45" captionTargetPageId-1="48" captionText-0="FIGURES 157 – 160. Male genitalia of Sphiximorpha garibaldii 157 Epandrium and hypandrium, holotype, lateral view 158 Surstyli, surstylar apodeme and cerci, holotype, ventral view 159 Epandrium, France, dorsal view 160 Surstyli, surstylar apodeme and cercisurstylar apodeme, France, ventral view. Scale line = 0.5 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 161 – 165. Male genitalia of Sphiximorpha subsessilis 161 Epandrium and hypandrium, lateral view 162 Aedeagus, lateral view 163 Epandrium, dorsal view 164 Epandrium, ventral view 165 Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/167955/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/167956/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">157–165</figureCitation>
): dorsal lobe of surstylus elongate, ventro-basal lobe large and rounded to rectangular shaped; dorsal lobe with scattered pile on apico-dorsal surface and setose on ventral surface; epandrium round with large membranous area; cercus elongate and triangular-shaped; surstylar apodeme rectangular, not fused, entirely but slightly sclerotized; hypandrium broad, with simple rounded superior lobe and short elongate lingula.
</paragraph>
